WEBVTT

00:06.099 --> 00:07.900
Darwin: Why do we have to
give them away?

00:07.934 --> 00:09.669
These toys
have sentimental value!

00:09.702 --> 00:11.737
It's not like anyone else
will love them like we do!

00:11.771 --> 00:14.207
Dude, we've locked them in the
attic for, like, seven years.

00:14.240 --> 00:16.876
Wow! Why did we ever stop
playing with this thing?!

00:16.909 --> 00:18.178
It was awesome!

00:18.211 --> 00:19.545
[ Up-tempo music plays ]
Twist me!

00:19.579 --> 00:21.914
[ Voice deepening ]
Hold me...

00:21.948 --> 00:24.217
[ Music slowing ]
Squeeze me...

00:24.250 --> 00:25.418
Mm.

00:25.451 --> 00:28.121
It never sounded as kid-friendly
after we dropped it.

00:28.154 --> 00:30.056
But, look, remember
our old digi-pet?

00:30.090 --> 00:33.859
We had to feed it and change
it's diaper and stuff!

00:33.893 --> 00:35.996
Hmm.
Out of batteries.

00:38.898 --> 00:40.366
[ Gasps ]
Mighty Flyz!

00:40.400 --> 00:42.868
♪ The warriors
that rule the skies ♪

00:42.902 --> 00:45.305
[ Screaming ]

00:48.008 --> 00:49.275
[ Bird squawks ]

00:49.309 --> 00:50.576
Mighty Flyz
takes no responsibility

00:50.610 --> 00:52.278
for any limbs, eyes,
or innocence lost

00:52.312 --> 00:54.080
when enjoying the Mighty Flyz
line of products.

00:54.114 --> 00:57.917
What else
could we give away?

00:57.950 --> 00:59.752
You've not seen them yet,
but, no.

00:59.785 --> 01:01.454
Seen what?
No!

01:01.487 --> 01:02.522
[ Grunts ]

01:02.555 --> 01:04.457
[ Gasps ]
Grady, Frank, and Howdy!

01:04.490 --> 01:05.825
Aw, Gumball,
we have to play with --

01:05.858 --> 01:06.859
No!

01:06.892 --> 01:08.194
But why?

01:08.228 --> 01:09.495
'Cause we're too old
to play with toys and dolls.

01:09.529 --> 01:11.297
Playing never goes
out of date.

01:11.331 --> 01:13.799
Playing with dolls means
you'll never go out on a date.

01:13.833 --> 01:14.900
[ Whimpers ]

01:14.934 --> 01:17.137
Come on, man.
Time to grow up.

01:17.170 --> 01:18.538
[ Sighs ]
You're right.

01:18.571 --> 01:20.473
I need to learn
to let things go.

01:20.506 --> 01:21.374
That's it.

01:21.407 --> 01:22.875
Trust me,
you'll thank me

01:22.908 --> 01:24.377
when your teenage years
kick in.

01:24.410 --> 01:26.446
I know.
[ Door closes ]

01:26.479 --> 01:28.614
[ Chuckles ]

01:28.648 --> 01:29.615
Hello, guys!

01:29.649 --> 01:32.152
[ Throwing voice ] Hello!
[ Coughing ]

01:32.185 --> 01:34.387
[ Normal voice ]
Ew! What's that smell?!

01:34.420 --> 01:36.456
[ Throwing voice ]
Morning breath can be quite bad

01:36.489 --> 01:39.592
when you've been asleep
in a shoe box for seven years!

01:39.625 --> 01:42.495
Come on, Frank, I'm sure Darwin
had a perfectly good reason

01:42.528 --> 01:44.764
to leave us in there
in endless darkness

01:44.797 --> 01:46.166
with only dust mites for food

01:46.199 --> 01:49.035
and our love
for him to keep us warm, right?

01:49.069 --> 01:50.936
[ Crunch ]
What was that?

01:50.970 --> 01:53.206
[ Normal voice ] That was
the weight of guilt, Howdy.

01:53.239 --> 01:54.407
[ Inhales ]

01:54.440 --> 01:55.775
I'm sorry.
We ditched you guys

01:55.808 --> 01:57.843
the Christmas we got our first
game console.

01:57.877 --> 02:00.646
[ Throwing voice ] That's okay.
We still love you.

02:00.680 --> 02:03.383
And you'll never put us back
in the box, will you?

02:03.416 --> 02:04.950
[ Normal voice ] I promise.

02:04.984 --> 02:07.887
[ Throwing voice ] And we'll
have fun forever and ever?

02:07.920 --> 02:09.155
[ Normal voice ] I promise.

02:09.189 --> 02:10.956
[ Throwing voice ]
And you'll never take us

02:10.990 --> 02:12.024
off your hands again, right?

02:12.058 --> 02:13.926
[ Normal voice ] I promise.

02:13.959 --> 02:16.896
[ Toilet flushes ]

02:16.929 --> 02:19.299
Sorry, but you did
make me promise.

02:19.332 --> 02:22.168
[ Upbeat music plays ]

02:26.872 --> 02:28.007
[ Gasps ]

02:28.040 --> 02:30.543
Ooh! Where have you been
all my life?

02:30.576 --> 02:33.246
Mmm, sitting here, wondering
what went wrong with mine,

02:33.279 --> 02:34.514
while eating cheese.

02:34.547 --> 02:37.817
Well, one ticket
to kiss-town, please.

02:37.850 --> 02:41.354
[ Romantic music plays ]

02:41.387 --> 02:42.822
[ Humming romantic tune ]

02:42.855 --> 02:45.024
What the?!
Dude!

02:45.057 --> 02:46.058
[ Truck horn blares ]

02:46.092 --> 02:47.127
[ Screams ]

02:47.160 --> 02:50.796
[ Crash ]

02:50.830 --> 02:51.897
[ Whispering ] Call me.

02:51.931 --> 02:53.266
[ Growls ]

02:53.299 --> 02:56.602
[ Grunting ]

02:56.636 --> 02:59.405
Dude, the school bus
is a total write-off!

02:59.439 --> 03:01.641
I guess that's what happens
when you put a 15-ton vehicle

03:01.674 --> 03:04.144
in the limp little hands
of a ventriloquist's dummy.

03:04.177 --> 03:06.979
[ Imitating Rocky ]

03:07.012 --> 03:09.549
[ Throwing voice ] Hey, what's
wrong with being a puppet?!

03:09.582 --> 03:11.317
Big talk
from someone so short

03:11.351 --> 03:13.719
you can see his feet
on his yearbook photo.

03:13.753 --> 03:14.687
What's your problem,
man?

03:14.720 --> 03:15.988
And what's with
the voice?

03:16.021 --> 03:17.423
My problem
is that your butt

03:17.457 --> 03:19.259
is twice as wide
as your shoulders,

03:19.292 --> 03:21.394
but your brain is half the size
of your head.

03:21.427 --> 03:22.595
Oh!
Anything else?

03:22.628 --> 03:24.697
No. I could try
to insult your face,

03:24.730 --> 03:27.600
but I think nature's
already done enough damage.

03:31.036 --> 03:32.605
At least
that solves the problem

03:32.638 --> 03:34.407
of how to eat
without your hands.

03:34.440 --> 03:35.775
Darwin: Oh, my goodness!

03:35.808 --> 03:38.178
Who skinned those puppets?!

03:38.211 --> 03:39.645
[ Normal voice ]
Shh! Those are my socks,

03:39.679 --> 03:42.215
and keep it down
or Gumball will hear you.

03:42.248 --> 03:44.417
Did you say something?
No.

03:44.450 --> 03:46.286
Then who were you
just talking to?

03:46.319 --> 03:47.753
[ Gurgling ]

03:47.787 --> 03:48.821
Nobody.

03:48.854 --> 03:50.590
[ Straining ]

03:53.659 --> 03:55.027
[ Gasping ]

03:55.060 --> 03:56.296
Ah, I knew it!

03:56.329 --> 03:58.198
Guys, you don't even
have lungs.

03:58.231 --> 04:00.700
[ Throwing voice ]
Oh, yeah!
Darwin,
we've been over this.

04:00.733 --> 04:02.802
You don't understand!
They're more than just --

04:02.835 --> 04:05.104
Darwin, dude, can you cover
yourself up first?!

04:05.137 --> 04:07.440
Oh, yeah, sorry.

04:07.473 --> 04:09.642
[ Throwing voice ] But Gumball,
we're more than just puppets!

04:09.675 --> 04:11.511
Darwin, you know
who talks through puppets?

04:11.544 --> 04:13.379
Crazy people and people
who want to make a living

04:13.413 --> 04:14.647
as a ventriloquist.

04:14.680 --> 04:16.616
So, yeah, crazy people,
basically.

04:16.649 --> 04:18.518
Gumball,
we need you, too.

04:18.551 --> 04:20.085
Who's gonna play
with Grady?

04:20.119 --> 04:21.387
Dude, no,
just take them off.

04:21.421 --> 04:24.857
No!
The fun will never end!

04:24.890 --> 04:26.125
Darwin, stop!

04:26.158 --> 04:28.127
Wait.
What are we doing?!

04:28.160 --> 04:29.629
[ Muffled ] Finally!
Thank you.

04:29.662 --> 04:32.298
You're supposed to fold over,
not under!

04:32.332 --> 04:34.234
[ Grunts ]
Frank, stop it!

04:34.267 --> 04:35.735
Ow!
No, you stop!

04:35.768 --> 04:37.237
[ Normal voice ]
You both stop!

04:37.270 --> 04:39.138
[ Throwing voice ]
Ow! No, you stop!

04:39.171 --> 04:40.640
[ Grunting ]

04:40.673 --> 04:42.375
Aha!

04:42.408 --> 04:44.410
[ Sighs ]
You used up all the water.

04:45.978 --> 04:47.480
[ Grunting ]

04:50.149 --> 04:51.183
[ Panting ]

04:51.217 --> 04:52.418
Darwin,
when I said grow up,

04:52.452 --> 04:54.119
I didn't mean
go straight to the part

04:54.153 --> 04:55.455
where you're
in a retirement home

04:55.488 --> 04:57.323
screaming at chairs
and biting the nurses!

04:57.357 --> 04:58.724
[ Normal voice ]
No! Please, don't do this!

04:58.758 --> 05:01.026
You don't understand!
They're alive!

05:01.060 --> 05:02.495
No, they are not!

05:02.528 --> 05:04.497
[ Throwing voice, muffled ]
No! Not the shoe box!

05:04.530 --> 05:06.999
It's almost as dark
as your soul in here!

05:07.032 --> 05:08.734
Oh!

05:08.768 --> 05:10.069
[ Normal voice ] Oh.

05:10.102 --> 05:12.638
Yeah, uh, dude, they're not
the ones who need help.

05:12.672 --> 05:14.307
[ Whimpers ]

05:15.941 --> 05:17.710
[ Snoring ]

05:20.012 --> 05:22.415
[ Clanging ]

05:23.749 --> 05:26.552
Frank, you okay?
You don't look quite yourself.

05:26.586 --> 05:29.789
Maybe there's something
I haven't digested properly.

05:29.822 --> 05:30.856
Whoa!

05:30.890 --> 05:32.458
Frank, wrong body!

05:32.492 --> 05:33.726
Oh...

05:33.759 --> 05:35.027
Okay, let's go.

05:35.060 --> 05:37.263
[ Grunting ]

05:37.297 --> 05:39.699
[ Door creaks ]

05:39.732 --> 05:43.002
Okay, the bedroom's
just at the top of the stairs.

05:43.035 --> 05:45.671
Wait.

05:45.705 --> 05:50.676
[ Crashing ]

05:50.710 --> 05:52.745
[ Gasps ]

05:52.778 --> 05:53.979
No!

05:59.051 --> 06:00.586
Come on, breathe!

06:00.620 --> 06:02.054
What have you done?!

06:02.087 --> 06:04.957
We taught that thing a lesson
for replacing us.

06:04.990 --> 06:06.158
I'm not talking to you!

06:06.191 --> 06:07.460
I'm talking to Darwin!

06:07.493 --> 06:09.795
Why did you go fish them
out of the trash?!

06:09.829 --> 06:12.197
He made a promise
never to abandon us.

06:12.231 --> 06:14.233
You can't make a promise
to an object!

06:14.266 --> 06:15.735
That's like getting married
to a fridge,

06:15.768 --> 06:17.337
or keeping a secret
for a shoe.

06:17.370 --> 06:19.472
And please stop talking
through these puppets!

06:19.505 --> 06:23.242
He can't.
He lives in our world now.

06:23.275 --> 06:25.277
And if you want to
see him again,

06:25.311 --> 06:29.815
you, too, will have to come
and play.

06:29.849 --> 06:31.784
[ Gasps ]
Darwin, wake up!

06:31.817 --> 06:33.519
Wake up!

06:41.694 --> 06:43.629
Thank you,
Master Gumball.

06:43.663 --> 06:46.098
I missed you greatly
all these years.

06:46.131 --> 06:49.234
Now, shall we go and find
Master Darwin?

06:49.268 --> 06:51.203
Wait, how do you know
what happened?

06:51.236 --> 06:53.539
Just because
I've been unable to talk

06:53.573 --> 06:56.776
does not mean
I've been unable to see.

06:56.809 --> 06:59.479
Remind me to apologize
to Anais' dolls.

06:59.512 --> 07:01.381
They're right next to my
underpants drawer.

07:01.414 --> 07:02.782
They've seen a lot.

07:08.187 --> 07:09.855
[ Screams ]
What the what?!

07:09.889 --> 07:12.324
What happened to me?!
Wait...

07:12.358 --> 07:14.059
[ Screams ]

07:14.093 --> 07:19.465
If that worried you, sir,
I advise you not to look down.

07:19.499 --> 07:20.700
Okay, Gumball.

07:20.733 --> 07:22.468
Focus on the task at hand --
not hand!

07:22.502 --> 07:25.304
Focus on the task a-hand.
Ahead -- task ahead!

07:25.337 --> 07:27.407
Shh...

07:27.440 --> 07:28.574
Shush.

07:28.608 --> 07:31.310
Can you hear that,
Master Gumball?

07:31.343 --> 07:32.945
[ Distant conversation, music ]

07:32.978 --> 07:34.480
This way.

07:34.514 --> 07:37.817
[ Both grunting ]

07:37.850 --> 07:41.854
Wow! Look at all the things we
imagined when we use to play.

07:41.887 --> 07:43.556
Hey, look!
High-five Guy!

07:43.589 --> 07:45.658
Ah, good to see you,
man.
[ Groans ]

07:45.691 --> 07:48.961
[ Gasps ] It's Sammy Sunscream,
the screaming sun!

07:48.994 --> 07:50.863
[ Sammy screaming ]

07:50.896 --> 07:52.498
The Tree
of Permanent Happiness!

07:52.532 --> 07:54.667
I wish I could feel
other things.

07:54.700 --> 07:56.836
[ Gasps ]
Bird-Plane-Bird!

07:56.869 --> 07:58.438
[ Squawks ]

07:58.471 --> 07:59.939
Please stay focused,
sir.

07:59.972 --> 08:01.140
Master Darwin needs you.

08:01.173 --> 08:02.307
Yeah, you're right.

08:02.341 --> 08:03.976
So stop distracting me,
Keyboard Dog.

08:04.009 --> 08:07.947
[ Barking ]
[ Random piano notes ]

08:09.449 --> 08:12.952
Here we are.

08:12.985 --> 08:14.520
♪ Dance around
and sing a song ♪

08:14.554 --> 08:16.656
♪ The fun
will never stop, yeah ♪

08:16.689 --> 08:18.524
♪ We have fun
all day long ♪

08:18.558 --> 08:20.325
♪ It says so
on the clock ♪

08:20.359 --> 08:22.562
♪ So wear a hat,
wear no hat ♪

08:22.595 --> 08:24.697
♪ Wear two hats,
if you'd prefer ♪

08:24.730 --> 08:27.767
♪ We only have two hats,
so those are your only options ♪

08:27.800 --> 08:29.935
♪ So put them on
and bake a cake ♪

08:29.969 --> 08:31.904
♪ And while you wait
for the cake to bake ♪

08:31.937 --> 08:33.606
♪ Begin to prepare
a second cake ♪

08:33.639 --> 08:37.109
You did it wrong
with that first cake.

08:37.142 --> 08:39.311
♪ It's your turn
with the balloon ♪

08:39.344 --> 08:41.313
♪ The fun will never end

08:41.346 --> 08:43.215
♪ Organize a spoon

08:43.248 --> 08:44.784
♪ The fun will never end

08:44.817 --> 08:46.752
♪ Count to
the funnest number ♪

08:46.786 --> 08:48.454
♪ The fun will never end

08:48.488 --> 08:50.389
♪ Go to
your favorite corner ♪

08:50.422 --> 08:52.357
♪ The fun will never end

08:52.391 --> 08:53.759
♪ I don't know
what's going on ♪

08:53.793 --> 08:55.628
♪ The fun will never end

08:55.661 --> 08:57.463
♪ I'm not sure
this is that fun ♪

08:57.497 --> 08:59.198
♪ The fun will never end

08:59.231 --> 09:00.666
[ Needle scratches ]

09:00.700 --> 09:01.801
What was that?

09:01.834 --> 09:03.936
A dramatic
record scratch sound.

09:03.969 --> 09:05.237
Dude, we gotta go!

09:05.270 --> 09:07.406
This is all a trap to keep you
playing with them forever!

09:07.439 --> 09:08.874
Grady: You're wrong.

09:08.908 --> 09:12.044
You see, there are three of us,
Master Gumball,

09:12.077 --> 09:14.446
and Darwin only has
two hands.

09:14.480 --> 09:18.217
This was a trap for you.

09:18.250 --> 09:21.987
Dum-dum-dum.

09:22.354 --> 09:23.756
What was that?

09:23.789 --> 09:26.025
A dramatic music cue.

09:26.058 --> 09:29.094
It would've been better
if my voice wasn't so flat.

09:29.128 --> 09:30.295
[ Doors slam ]

09:30.329 --> 09:32.665
♪ You always used to
play with us ♪

09:32.698 --> 09:34.867
♪ And now it's our turn
to play with you ♪

09:34.900 --> 09:37.202
♪ So play along,
don't make a fuss ♪

09:37.236 --> 09:39.304
♪ And we'll come up
with things to do ♪

09:39.338 --> 09:41.674
♪ We'll make you dance,
we'll make you fight ♪

09:41.707 --> 09:43.843
♪ You'll smear yourselves
with worms all night ♪

09:43.876 --> 09:46.045
♪ We'll make you
eat toenails and grease ♪

09:46.078 --> 09:48.313
♪ We'll make you wear
an itchy fleece ♪

09:48.347 --> 09:50.883
♪ We'll see if you break
when you bend ♪

09:50.916 --> 09:52.918
♪ The fun will never end

09:52.952 --> 09:55.154
♪ The fun will ne--

09:55.187 --> 09:56.388
Wait, what's that?

09:56.421 --> 09:58.591
The end of the fun.

09:58.624 --> 10:00.960
[ Gasps ]

10:03.262 --> 10:04.363
Run!

10:04.396 --> 10:05.631
[ Both panting ]

10:05.665 --> 10:08.834
[ Screams ]

10:08.868 --> 10:11.370
All: No!

10:12.304 --> 10:14.306
Is it me, or is that kind of
underwhelming?

10:14.339 --> 10:15.474
Yeah. I sort of thought

10:15.507 --> 10:16.942
everything would explode
or something.

10:16.976 --> 10:19.111
Wait.
Isn't this all imaginary?

10:19.144 --> 10:20.312
Oh, good point.

10:20.345 --> 10:21.647
All: No!

10:21.681 --> 10:24.950
Grady:
I will have my revenge!

10:31.891 --> 10:33.726
Oh!

10:33.759 --> 10:37.697
Sure you're okay with me
giving away your old toys?

10:37.730 --> 10:39.298
[ Screaming ]

10:39.331 --> 10:40.866
Both: Yeah, pretty sure.

10:41.266 --> 10:44.069
[ Theme music plays ]
